node.text:
Hey StarReaders! 😉 ⭐ 
We hope you didn't miss our first & second episode from the Star Stable Master Class with author @helenadahlgrenofficial. Here's the first episode for you to learn from now or save for later, to enjoy during your cozy weekend! 📖

If you've already dived into our Star Stable Master Class, we're happy to let you know that Episodes 3 & 4 will come out soon, stay tuned! 🤩

Not only is this Star Stable Master Class full of awesome advice, but we hope it encourages you to write your own story! Put your learnings to the test by joining our ongoing storytelling challenge. Take part in our short
story competition for the chance to have your story turned into an
Instagram comic by illustrator Elli Puukangaas! @ellipuukangas #SSOStoryTellers #ReadWriteUnite

node.title: Star Stable Master Class: From reader to writer

node.text:
Happy Wednesday, StarFam! We’ve all been waiting, and now it’s time for the return of the beloved trail ride event known as the Red String Trail Ride!

To symbolize the unbreakable bond between friends or a rider and their horse, it’s tradition to follow a trail up in the Firgrove mountains and tie a red string at the end. This tradition is known as the Red String Trail Ride and is a celebrated event amongst Jorvegian riders!

You start the Red String Trail Ride by signing up at the trail ride board to get a red string, and finish the ride by tying the string at the end of the trail!

Hey StarFam! It's that time again — the Jorvik Stables Open House is here! It's open for all visitors until the Wednesday Update on August 4th. 

We all know Johanna at the Jorvik Stables to be an excellent project manager, but we also know that the Open House is a huge event, and sometimes it’s nice to have friends to help you out. Go talk to Johanna and make sure everything is in order before the visitors arrive!

The beautiful Open House arena is a fan favorite and it’s back again! In this huge arena you can practise your drill team skills with your friends, take beautiful pictures, or why not practise a dressage routine you might try out in real life later? The arena will feature brand-new Kür music made just for dressage! The music is produced by Matilda Frommegård, acclaimed composer of Kür!

During these two weeks, six lovely horses are available to buy at the Jorvik Stables! If you joined the event last year, you’ll recognize six of them, but a brand new Arabian has decided to join in on the fun!

The three grey Generation 2 Lipizzaner horses are available for 949 Star Coins each. The Generation 3 Lusitano is available in the colors fleabitten grey and liver chestnut, and go for 949 Star Coins each. The Generation 3 buckskin Andalusian will be yours for 950 Star Coins. The Generation 3 black rabicano Arabian will be yours for 950 Star Coins. #AwesomeArabians 

The special Open House shop is back, and it now offers two new baroque inspired outfit sets in new colors! All items you previously have been able to find in the shop will also be available. Andy’s popular petting zoo is also back.
